it may be thy expre&s;&s;ion flows from thy experience; but I &s;hall never take that Mari|ner for my Pil<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t, that hath no better knowledge than the &s;plitting of his own Ship W<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> thou condemn the f<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ame of all for the faults of one? as if it were true Logick, b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">|cau&s;e &s;ome are evil, therefore none are good. He hath ill eyes that di&s;dains all object<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc; To bla&s;t thy helper, is to blame thy Maker. In a
